I'm a straight guy so you can imagine I don't get my nails done too often. But I had some guests at the hotel that wanted to go. Reservations recommended Mirage. I drove them there and they said I HAD to join them and get a pedicure. They said they would even pay for it. I was skeptical, and also on the clock. But I took a risk and laid down. Best bad decision I ever made. The massage was on point. Each chair had a little foot bath with warm water. The whole joint is decorated with water and dolphins. 2 huge flat screens. This place was COMFORTABLE! I even warned them about my in-grown toe nail. Not only did my nail tech take care with my painful spot, she completely removed the in-grown! I didn't know they could do that! I can walk normal again! This place is awesome. Definite recommendation. 10/10 stars, class A rating, friendly personal staff with a cool atmosphere!

